01/02/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- Greek Orthodox Church leader Archbishop Christodoulos, who died of liver cancer on Monday at the age of 69, was buried on Thursday (January 31st). Schools, government institutions and courts were closed as the archbishop was buried with honours that are typically reserved for a head of state. The procession was joined by tens of thousands of people who came to Athens from across the country. (ANA-MPA, ERT, Euronews, Press TV, AP, Antena - 31/01/08)
